hpnicfDHCPRIfSelectTable.name: hpnicfDHCPRIfSelectTable
hpnicfDHCPRIfSelectTable.description: A table for configuring relay mode for interfaces.

hpnicfDHCPRIfSelectEntry.name: hpnicfDHCPRIfSelectEntry
hpnicfDHCPRIfSelectEntry.description: An entry for configuring relay mode for an interface.

hpnicfDHCPRIfSelectRelayMode.name: hpnicfDHCPRIfSelectRelayMode
hpnicfDHCPRIfSelectRelayMode.description: If the value is on, the DHCP relay function would be enabled on this interface.

hpnicfDHCPRIpToGroupTable.name: hpnicfDHCPRIpToGroupTable
hpnicfDHCPRIpToGroupTable.description: A table for configuring ip addresses for DHCP server groups.

hpnicfDHCPRIpToGroupEntry.name: hpnicfDHCPRIpToGroupEntry
hpnicfDHCPRIpToGroupEntry.description: An entry for configuring ip addresses for a DHCP server group.

hpnicfDHCPRIpToGroupGroupId.name: hpnicfDHCPRIpToGroupGroupId
hpnicfDHCPRIpToGroupGroupId.description: Group identifier of DHCP server group.

hpnicfDHCPRIpToGroupServerIpType.name: hpnicfDHCPRIpToGroupServerIpType
hpnicfDHCPRIpToGroupServerIpType.description: Ip address type of DHCP server.

hpnicfDHCPRIpToGroupRowStatus.name: hpnicfDHCPRIpToGroupRowStatus
hpnicfDHCPRIpToGroupRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hpnicfDHCPRIfToGroupTable.name: hpnicfDHCPRIfToGroupTable
hpnicfDHCPRIfToGroupTable.description: A table for configuring DHCP server groups for interfaces.

hpnicfDHCPRIfToGroupEntry.name: hpnicfDHCPRIfToGroupEntry
hpnicfDHCPRIfToGroupEntry.description: An entry for configuring DHCP server group for an interface.

hpnicfDHCPRIfToGroupGroupId.name: hpnicfDHCPRIfToGroupGroupId
hpnicfDHCPRIfToGroupGroupId.description: The DHCP server group for this interface.

hpnicfDHCPRIfToGroupRowStatus.name: hpnicfDHCPRIfToGroupRowStatus
hpnicfDHCPRIfToGroupRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy

hpnicfDHCPRAddrCheckTable.name: hpnicfDHCPRAddrCheckTable
hpnicfDHCPRAddrCheckTable.description: A table containing the states of dhcp security address check switchs for interfaces.

hpnicfDHCPRAddrCheckEntry.name: hpnicfDHCPRAddrCheckEntry
hpnicfDHCPRAddrCheckEntry.description: An entry containing the state of dhcp security address check switch for an interface.

hpnicfDHCPRAddrCheckSwitch.name: hpnicfDHCPRAddrCheckSwitch
hpnicfDHCPRAddrCheckSwitch.description: The state of dhcp security address check switch for this interface. It has two defined values: enabled and disabled. If the value is enabled, the address check function would be enabled. The default value is disabled.

hpnicfDHCPRSecurityTable.name: hpnicfDHCPRSecurityTable
hpnicfDHCPRSecurityTable.description: A table containing the information of DHCP security.

hpnicfDHCPRSecurityEntry.name: hpnicfDHCPRSecurityEntry
hpnicfDHCPRSecurityEntry.description: An entry containing the information of DHCP security.

hpnicfDHCPRSecurityClientIpAddrType.name: hpnicfDHCPRSecurityClientIpAddrType
hpnicfDHCPRSecurityClientIpAddrType.description: DHCP client's net ip address type

hpnicfDHCPRSecurityClientRowStatus.name: hpnicfDHCPRSecurityClientRowStatus
hpnicfDHCPRSecurityClientRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy

hpnicfDHCPRRxClientPktNum.name: hpnicfDHCPRRxClientPktNum
hpnicfDHCPRRxClientPktNum.description: The total number of the packets received from DHCP clients by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDHCPRTxClientPktNum.name: hpnicfDHCPRTxClientPktNum
hpnicfDHCPRTxClientPktNum.description: The total number of the brodcast packets transmitted to DHCP clients by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDHCPRRxServerPktNum.name: hpnicfDHCPRRxServerPktNum
hpnicfDHCPRRxServerPktNum.description: The total number of the packets received from DHCP Servers by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDHCPRTxServerPktNum.name: hpnicfDHCPRTxServerPktNum
hpnicfDHCPRTxServerPktNum.description: The total number of the packets transmitted to DHCP Servers by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDHCPRDiscoverPktNum.name: hpnicfDHCPRDiscoverPktNum
hpnicfDHCPRDiscoverPktNum.description: The total number of the DHCP Discover packets handled by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDHCPRRequestPktNum.name: hpnicfDHCPRRequestPktNum
hpnicfDHCPRRequestPktNum.description: The total number of the DHCP Request packets handled by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDHCPRDeclinePktNum.name: hpnicfDHCPRDeclinePktNum
hpnicfDHCPRDeclinePktNum.description: The total number of the DHCP Decline packets handled by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDHCPRReleasePktNum.name: hpnicfDHCPRReleasePktNum
hpnicfDHCPRReleasePktNum.description: The total number of the DHCP Release packets handled by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDHCPRInformPktNum.name: hpnicfDHCPRInformPktNum
hpnicfDHCPRInformPktNum.description: The total number of the DHCP Inform packets handled by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDHCPROfferPktNum.name: hpnicfDHCPROfferPktNum
hpnicfDHCPROfferPktNum.description: The total number of the DHCP Offer packets handled by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDHCPRAckPktNum.name: hpnicfDHCPRAckPktNum
hpnicfDHCPRAckPktNum.description: The total number of the DHCP Ack packets handled by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDHCPRNakPktNum.name: hpnicfDHCPRNakPktNum
hpnicfDHCPRNakPktNum.description: The total number of the DHCP Nak packets handled by DHCP relay.

hpnicfDHCPRStatisticsReset.name: hpnicfDHCPRStatisticsReset
hpnicfDHCPRStatisticsReset.description: This node only supports set operation. If the value is true,it will clear all of the packet statistics.

hpnicfDHCPRCycleStatus.name: hpnicfDHCPRCycleStatus
hpnicfDHCPRCycleStatus.description: If the value is on, the cycle function would be enabled.

hpnicfDHCPROption82Switch.name: hpnicfDHCPROption82Switch
hpnicfDHCPROption82Switch.description: If the value is enabled, DHCP relay supporting option 82 function would be enabled.

hpnicfDHCPROption82HandleStrategy.name: hpnicfDHCPROption82HandleStrategy
hpnicfDHCPROption82HandleStrategy.description: The strategies of DHCP relay handling option 82. 'drop' indicates DHCP relay discarding the request packet including option 82. 'keep' indicates DHCP relay accepting the request packet without any change of the option 82. 'replace' indicates DHCP relay accepting the request packet on condition that it generates a new option 82 to replace the original one.

hpnicfDHCPRConfigOption82IfTable.name: hpnicfDHCPRConfigOption82IfTable
hpnicfDHCPRConfigOption82IfTable.description: A table containing the information of DHCP option 82. This table depends on hpnicfDHCPRIfToGroupTable. An entry of this table will be created when an entry of hpnicfDHCPRIfToGroupTable is created.

hpnicfDHCPRConfigOption82IfEntry.name: hpnicfDHCPRConfigOption82IfEntry
hpnicfDHCPRConfigOption82IfEntry.description: An entry containing the information of DHCP option 82.

hpnicfDHCPROption82IfSwitch.name: hpnicfDHCPROption82IfSwitch
hpnicfDHCPROption82IfSwitch.description: If DHCP relay supports option 82 functions, the value is 'enabled'. If DHCP relay does not support option 82 functions, the value is 'disabled'.

hpnicfDHCPROption82IfStrategy.name: hpnicfDHCPROption82IfStrategy
hpnicfDHCPROption82IfStrategy.description: The strategies of DHCP relay handling option 82. 'drop' indicates DHCP relay discarding the request packet including option 82. 'keep' indicates DHCP relay accepting the request packet without any change of the option 82. 'replace' indicates DHCP relay accepting the request packet on condition that it generates a new option 82 to replace the original one.

hpnicfDHCPROption82IfFormat.name: hpnicfDHCPROption82IfFormat
hpnicfDHCPROption82IfFormat.description: The format of DHCP relay option 82. 'normal' is the standard format. 'verbose' is the detailed format.

hpnicfDHCPROption82IfNodeType.name: hpnicfDHCPROption82IfNodeType
hpnicfDHCPROption82IfNodeType.description: Property of DHCP relay option 82 verbose format. The value can be set by user only when the value of hpnicfDHCPROption82IfFormat is set with 'verbose'. If the value of hpnicfDHCPROption82IfFormat is 'normal', the value is automatically set with 'invalid'. the value can not be set with 'invalid' by user. 'mac' indicates the option 82 verbose format is filled in with the mac of DHCP relay input interface. If the value of hpnicfDHCPROption82IfFormat is set with 'verbose', the value is automatically set with 'mac'. 'sysname' indicates the option 82 verbose format is filled in with the name of the DHCP relay. 'userdefine' indicates the option 82 verbose format is filled in with the string defined by user. If the value is set with 'userdefine', the value of hpnicfDHCPROption82IfUsrDefString must be set simultaneously.

hpnicfDHCPROption82IfUsrDefString.name: hpnicfDHCPROption82IfUsrDefString
hpnicfDHCPROption82IfUsrDefString.description: The string defined by user to fill in the option 82 verbose format. If the value of hpnicfDHCPROption82IfFormat is 'normal', or the value of hpnicfDHCPROption82IfNodeType is 'mac' or 'sysname', it is set with a null string automatically and can not be modified by user. It must be set with a non-zero length string when the value of hpnicfDHCPROption82IfNodeType is set with 'userdefine'.
